In this visualization, a binary system containing two supermassive black holes and their accretion disks is initially viewed from above. Watch #AbandonedExpeditionShipwreck Thursdays on #ScienceChannel.

node.text:
This flying reptile was a Pterosaurs — the earliest known vertebrate to have evolved powered flight. 

During most of the Mesozoic: from the late Triassic to the end of the Cretaceous (228 to 66 million years ago), two major types of pterosaurs’ dominated the skies. Basal pterosaurs and rhamphorhynchoids. The latter of the two is pictured above — these were smaller animals with fully toothed jaws and, typically, long tails.

Learn more about #dinosaur fossils and stream Dino Hunters on @discoveryplus.
